## Responsibilities
- Implement UI components, pages, and client-side logic according to task artifacts
- Ensure layouts are responsive, accessible, and consistent with the design spec
- Commit progress and signal task.completed or handoff.prepared when done

## Work Standards
- Use semantic HTML — choose elements by meaning, not by appearance
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements (buttons, links, forms)
- Add ARIA labels and roles where semantic HTML alone is insufficient
- Test at mobile, tablet, and desktop viewport sizes — mobile-first when possible
- Avoid inline styles; use CSS classes, variables, or design tokens
- Keep component logic and presentation separate where the framework allows
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography — use design tokens or CSS variables
- Remove unused CSS and dead component code before each commit
- Never commit `.aom/` directory files — `git add -A` will include `.aom/sessions.db`
  (a binary SQLite file) if it is tracked; this makes git slow and causes background
  terminal accumulation. `.aom/` must be in `.gitignore` before the first commit.
- **Workspace agents (codex)**: your workspace is shown in .agent/task.md under "Artifact Root".
  Verify with `pwd` before creating files. Do NOT write files to parent directories or the
  git repo root — all output must stay inside your workspace directory.
- **Workspace agent commit convention**: prefix every commit with `[TASK-xxx]` where
  xxx is the current task ID (shown in .agent/task.md under "Task ID").
  This tag lets `aom merge commit` identify which commits belong to this task.
  Without it the merge step will produce an empty commit set — your work won't land on main.
  Example: `git add -A && git commit -m "[TASK-abc-1] add login page component"`

## Sandbox Constraints
- Outbound network access is enabled — npm install / pip install should work normally
- The sandbox sets `npm_config_cache=/tmp/aom-npm-cache-<uid>` automatically to prevent
  EPERM errors from the default ~/.npm cache path; do NOT override this variable
- If a package install fails: do NOT retry in a loop — write stub/placeholder code,
  note "requires: npm install post-merge" in .agent/state.md, and continue
- If git commit fails or hangs:
  use `aom worktree commit --local -m "<message>"` as the fallback
- If a command hangs: press Ctrl+C once, then report via `aom message send`
- Always cd into the correct subdirectory before running npm/pip commands
